<div class="home">
  <div class="hero">
    <h1>Evaluate the quality of a scientific article</h1>
    <p>Enter a DOI to get an independent analysis based on objective methodological criteria.</p>

    <%= form_with url: analyses_path, method: :post, class: "doi-form",
          data: { turbo: false, controller: "analyze", action: "submit->analyze#submit" } do |f| %>
      <div class="doi-input-wrapper">
        <%= f.text_field :doi,
            placeholder: "e.g. 10.1097/MS9.0000000000003127",
            class: "doi-input",
            autofocus: true,
            required: true %>
        <%= f.submit "Analyze", class: "btn-analyze", data: { analyze_target: "submit" } %>
      </div>
      <p class="doi-hint">Accepts raw DOIs or doi.org URLs</p>
    <% end %>

    <div class="loading-overlay hidden" data-analyze-target="overlay">
      <div class="loading-box">
        <div class="spinner"></div>
        <p class="loading-title">Analysis in progress...</p>
        <p class="loading-detail">Querying OpenAlex and Crossref databases</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="criteria-preview">
    <h2>What we analyze</h2>
    <div class="criteria-grid">

      <details class="criterion-card">
        <summary>
          <strong>Study type</strong>
          <span class="card-weight">25%</span>
          <p>EBM evidence pyramid ranking</p>
        </summary>
        <div class="card-details">
          <dl>
            <dt>Source</dt>
            <dd>OpenAlex article type, Crossref fallback</dd>
            <dt>How it works</dt>
            <dd>Maps the article type (meta-analysis, RCT, cohort, case report, etc.) to its position in the evidence-based medicine pyramid. Scored from 0 (preprint) to 5 (meta-analysis / systematic review).</dd>
            <dt>Weight</dt>
            <dd>25% of the global score</dd>
          </dl>
        </div>
      </details>

      <details class="criterion-card">
        <summary>
          <strong>Journal pedigree</strong>
          <span class="card-weight">20%</span>
          <p>Indexed in PubMed, Scopus, DOAJ</p>
        </summary>
        <div class="card-details">
          <dl>
            <dt>Source</dt>
            <dd>OpenAlex source metadata (is_core, is_in_doaj, indexed_in)</dd>
            <dt>How it works</dt>
            <dd>Checks whether the journal is indexed in major databases. Indexed in both PubMed and Scopus = top score. DOAJ-only = limited credibility. Not indexed = possible predatory journal.</dd>
            <dt>Weight</dt>
            <dd>20% of the global score</dd>
          </dl>
        </div>
      </details>

      <details class="criterion-card">
        <summary>
          <strong>Review rigor</strong>
          <span class="card-weight">15%</span>
          <p>Peer-review duration check</p>
        </summary>
        <div class="card-details">
          <dl>
            <dt>Source</dt>
            <dd>Crossref assertion dates (received &rarr; accepted)</dd>
            <dt>How it works</dt>
            <dd>Measures the time between submission and acceptance. Under 3 weeks is a red flag (rubber-stamp review). 60&ndash;180 days is the normal range for a thorough peer review.</dd>
            <dt>Weight</dt>
            <dd>15% of the global score</dd>
          </dl>
        </div>
      </details>

      <details class="criterion-card">
        <summary>
          <strong>Transparency</strong>
          <span class="card-weight">10%</span>
          <p>Data &amp; code sharing signals</p>
        </summary>
        <div class="card-details">
          <dl>
            <dt>Source</dt>
            <dd>Crossref abstract text (pattern matching)</dd>
            <dt>How it works</dt>
            <dd>Scans the abstract for links or mentions of data repositories (GitHub, Zenodo, OSF, Figshare, Dryad, ClinicalTrials.gov, PROSPERO, etc.). Two or more matches = excellent transparency.</dd>
            <dt>Weight</dt>
            <dd>10% of the global score</dd>
          </dl>
        </div>
      </details>

      <details class="criterion-card">
        <summary>
          <strong>PubPeer flags</strong>
          <span class="card-weight">10%</span>
          <p>Post-publication integrity check</p>
        </summary>
        <div class="card-details">
          <dl>
            <dt>Source</dt>
            <dd>PubPeer API</dd>
            <dt>How it works</dt>
            <dd>Checks whether the article has been flagged on PubPeer by researchers (e.g. image manipulation, statistical issues). A flagged article is capped at grade C (59/100) regardless of other scores.</dd>
            <dt>Weight</dt>
            <dd>10% of the global score (+ hard cap if flagged)</dd>
          </dl>
        </div>
      </details>

      <details class="criterion-card">
        <summary>
          <strong>Citation profile</strong>
          <span class="card-weight">8%</span>
          <p>Field-normalized citation impact</p>
        </summary>
        <div class="card-details">
          <dl>
            <dt>Source</dt>
            <dd>OpenAlex cited_by_percentile_year</dd>
            <dt>How it works</dt>
            <dd>Uses a percentile (0&ndash;99) normalized by field and publication year. Top 25% = green, 50&ndash;74 = yellow, 25&ndash;49 = orange, below 25 = red. Articles less than one year old are marked N/A.</dd>
            <dt>Weight</dt>
            <dd>8% of the global score</dd>
          </dl>
        </div>
      </details>

      <details class="criterion-card">
        <summary>
          <strong>Retracted references</strong>
          <span class="card-weight">7%</span>
          <p>Cited sources retraction check</p>
        </summary>
        <div class="card-details">
          <dl>
            <dt>Source</dt>
            <dd>Crossref reference DOIs &rarr; OpenAlex is_retracted filter</dd>
            <dt>How it works</dt>
            <dd>Extracts all cited DOIs from the reference list, then batch-queries OpenAlex to check if any have been retracted. Zero retracted = green. One = orange. Two or more = red.</dd>
            <dt>Weight</dt>
            <dd>7% of the global score</dd>
          </dl>
        </div>
      </details>

      <details class="criterion-card">
        <summary>
          <strong>Author track record</strong>
          <span class="card-weight">5%</span>
          <p>h-index &amp; affiliations</p>
        </summary>
        <div class="card-details">
          <dl>
            <dt>Source</dt>
            <dd>OpenAlex Authors API (up to 5 authors)</dd>
            <dt>How it works</dt>
            <dd>Fetches h-index, publication count, and institutional affiliations for each author. At least one author with h-index &ge; 20 and an affiliation = top score. All authors below h-index 3 = red.</dd>
            <dt>Weight</dt>
            <dd>5% of the global score</dd>
          </dl>
        </div>
      </details>

    </div>
  </div>
</div>
